DIV1.P:
I have only to add, that I wish you an un∣tarnished Bliss in the Company of your po∣lished Friend, and that you may enjoy each
other's Friendship even to the Age of old NESTOR,
Whose Tongue dropp'd Honey; full of Days was he;
Two Ages past, he liv'd the Third to see;
And, his first Race of Subjects long decay'd,
O'er their Sons' Sons a peacefull Scepter sway'd. POPE's Homer.

Yesterday, I had the Company of Miss LEA, and Mr. HILTON, a very
modest and ingenious Man, who came with Lord DUD∣LEY from London;
besides two other Parties of Visitants, who engrossed my whole Day.

BEING gone for a few Days to Hampton-Court, I did not
receive the Favour of yours so soon as you might naturally imagine,
consequently it was not in my Power to write to you by the returning Post;
and ever since being full of Employment, I deferred that Pleasure till the
present Moment, which I fear will produce little worth your Attention;
how∣ever, such as it is I give unto you.
